burning-plains.html.title: Burning Plains
burning-plains.html.description: area based on Zdzislaw Beksinski art Burning City ruins of a city eternally burning Plains wide open plains with occasional ruins and leafless trees

dimensional-decay.html.title: Dimensional Decay
dimensional-decay.html.description: Dimensional Decay is the process of a dimensions temporal stability degrading as a result of objects "leaking" between dimensions this requires the use of Scrapers to eliminate the undesirable effects this puts a soft timer on scraping missions with the player slowly beginning to take damage from the instability similar to pacific drives mechanics

dimensional-portals.html.title: Dimensional portals
dimensional-portals.html.description:
Dimension Portals are the main mode of transport between dimensions
each portal starts deactivated and must be manually reactivated

forest.html.title: Forest
forest.html.description:
The forest is the staring dimension of the game and the main home base of the local scrapersSubareasMain Base main base of operations for local scrappers made out of a converted gas station upgrades and missions are gained here its a more rural scraper outpost that has semi-recently been established to deal with the rise of dimensional leaks Forests thick forests surrounding the main base dirt roads are carved through the terrain by scrapper trucks, the ground is covered by a thick moss and covered by winding vines and fallen trees
Abandoned Bunkers
overgrown concrete bunkers in the deep forest, dark and dangerous but contain valuable scrap use dynamite to clear collapsed passages and reveal the most unstable scrap

main.html.title: Main
main.html.description:
Name: Codename: ScrapperDesc: this game is a smaller 3d scrap colleting game similar to lethal company but the main mode of transport is a largescrap hauler vehicle. the main gameplay loop consists of finding scraped that has leaked over from other dimensions and returning them to their dimension of origin for a reward.Major Mechanics Driving
Dimensional portals
Dimensional Decay Unique Scrap Mechanics
Upgrade System Graphics the main style of the game is a simple Vector style with sharp clean textures and hard shadowsDimensions
Forest
Negative
Spikes
Morel
Void Wind
Mirror
Burning Plains

mirror.html.title: Mirror
mirror.html.description: this dimension is a land of mirror water and two mirrored worlds driving or jumping into a mirror lake leads to the mirror region of the world with you on the ceiling when you where on the floor Mirror fish slowly swim through the sky maze somewhere white and blue color scheme

morel.html.title: Morel
morel.html.description: large landmass of tunnels resembling a morel mushroom gravity is relative to the nearest face and does not have a global "down" the caves walls are thin yet strong and you can find occasional deposits of a resinous substance

scrap-hauler-vehicle.html.title: scrap hauler vehicle
scrap-hauler-vehicle.html.description: The Scrap Hauler Vehicle or SHV is the main mode of transporting scrap collected in the game. The vehicle has a large flatbed back and a half track drivetrain with a integrated crane built into the front half of the vehicleexample photo of drivetrain (back track may be mildly elongated in final version)

scrapers.html.title: Scrapers
scrapers.html.description: group of people tasked with collecting unstable scrap to prevent dimensional Decay mostly decentralized organization, not "secretly they are the bad guys" they just kinda exist

spikes.html.title: Spikes
spikes.html.description: barren flat plains with large spiky shining metal spikes the metal hums and shivers and you can hear twisting and creaking in the distance dry cracked grey ground with the occasional rock

upgrade-system.html.title: Upgrade System
upgrade-system.html.description:
Upgadesreduced bounciness for items in truck
increased speed
scrap scanner

void-wind.html.title: Void Wind
void-wind.html.description: A web of thin paths over an endless void. Storms rage in the sky and lightning strikes often creating lightning glass a valuable resource. Scrap can be found floating and can be captured to a netgun grey and dark blue with purple lightning

info_showOrphanNodes.description: Show nodes that are not connected to any other nodes.

info_showAttachments.description: Show attachments like images and PDFs as nodes in the graph.

info_allowGlobalGraph.description: Allow the user to view the global graph of all nodes.

info_allowExpand.description: Allow the user to pop-out the graph view to take up the whole screen

info_attractionForce.description: How much should linked nodes attract each other? This will make the graph appear more clustered.

info_linkLength.description: How long should the links between nodes be? The shorter the links the more connected nodes will cluster together.

info_repulsionForce.description: How much should nodes repel each other? This will make disconnected parts more spread out.

info_centralForce.description: How much should nodes be attracted to the center? This will make the graph appear more dense and circular.

info_edgePruning.description: Edges with a length above this threshold will not be rendered, however they will still contribute to the simulation. This can help large tangled graphs look more organised. Hovering over a node will still display these links.

info_minNodeRadius.description: How small should the smallest nodes be? The smaller a node is the less it will attract other nodes.

info_maxNodeRadius.description: How large should the largest nodes be? Nodes are sized by how many links they have. The larger a node is the more it will attract other nodes. This can be used to create a good grouping around the most important nodes.
